metadata.name: Layers of New York #1: High Line, NYC
metadata.description:
The High Line is an elevated freight rail line transformed into a public park on Manhattan's West Side. It has become one of the most beloved parks in Manhattan, and it stimulated a transformation of the neighborhoods around it. As more and more modern constructions replace the older buildings in that area, My Layer of New York series took a nostalgic view honoring the history of the city and its neighborhoods.

Format: PNG / Resolution: 3168x4642
